essentially a systemic disease. These include duodenal and peri-ampullary 
adenomas and carcinoma, desmoid tumors, papillary-type thyroid carcinoma and 
pancreatic carcinoma among others. With improved management that reduces the 
risk of colorectal cancer, these extracolonic manifestations have become of 
increasing clinical significance. For all FAP patients, including those 
undergoing proctocolectomy, thorough surveillance is of vital importance as 
there remains a risk of developing neoplasia. Despite advances in surgical 
techniques, screening and surveillance, life expectancy in patients with FAP is 
still less than that of the general population.

